feat: v0.6.0 production-ready release

All critical bugs fixed, tested, ready to deploy.

Core fixes:
- Real asyncio.timeout() wrapping every tool call
- Race-condition-safe per-user locking via global lock
- Session TTL enforcement + max pool size eviction
- Dynamic tool discovery via session.list_tools()
- Dynamic tool_args (no longer hardcoded)
- Proper JSON serialization with default=str
- Graceful cleanup_all() on shutdown

Worker (was a stub, now real):
- process_job() actually runs MCP tool calls
- Stores results in Redis with configurable TTL
- Status tracking: queued, running, completed, failed

New API endpoints:
- GET /job/{job_id} poll background job status/results
- GET /tools/{user_id} list available MCP tools
- DELETE /session/{user_id} manual session cleanup
- Enhanced GET /health with session count

Infrastructure:
- CI: Added Redis service container for tests
- Dockerfile: Removed redundant COPY
- Tests: 6 tests, all mocked, 0 warnings
- Pydantic V2 ConfigDict

TypeScript:
- Fixed ioredis import
- Added real timeout + background job queueing
- Added error handling, session cleanup, health endpoint

Removed:
- Broken vercel.json
- False marketing claims from README
- Dead code in app.py
